    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><p><b>Problem description.</b></p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FF69B4;\">Shrirupa</span> loves to celebrate Diwali every year. Besides burning crackers, she likes the lighting which shows up around this time. In order to light up the verandah, <span style=\"color:#FF69B4;\">Shrirupa</span> had bought many diyas and candles when the festival was on. Even after it is over, she is left with <b>\u2018d\u2019</b> diyas and <b>\u2018c\u2019</b> candles. Today she has decided to light all that is left, and arrange those in a single row in her verandah. \u00a0</p>\n<p>However, <span style=\"color:#FF69B4;\">Shrirupa</span> was a bit tired and she asked her friend <span style=\"color:#00FF00;\">Rohit</span> to help her out. <span style=\"color:#00FF00;\">Rohit</span> thinks that the arrangement will look <b>awesome</b> only if there are atmost <b>\u2018n1'</b>diyas, and atmost <b>\u2018n2\u2019</b> candles adjacently lined up together i.e., if there are more than <b>n1</b> diyas, or more than <b>n2</b> candles standing together<b>(successively one after another)</b>, then the arrangement will not look <b>awesome</b>.</p>\n<p>He wants to bring smile on her face by making an awesome arrangement. So, find the number of ways in which <span style=\"color:#00FF00;\">Rohit</span> can arrange <b>d</b> diyas and <b>c</b> candles so that it looks <b>awesome</b>, and <span style=\"color:#FF69B4;\">Shrirupa's</span> face lights up with smile .</p>\n\n<h3>Input</h3>\n<p>First line contains four space separated integers <b>d</b>,<b>c</b>,<b>n1</b>,<b>n2</b> where <b>d</b>,<b>c</b> denotes the no. of diyas and candles left with <span style=\"color:#FF69B4;\">Shrirupa</span>, and <b>n1</b>,<b>n2</b> denotes the largest no. of diyas and candles which can be put up in <b>succession(together)</b>, respectively.</p>\n<p></p>\n\n<h3>Output</h3>\n<p>Print the total no.of <b>awesome</b> arrangements modulo <b>10^9 + 7</b>, such that atmost <b>n1</b> diyas and <b>n2</b> candles stand <b>successively</b>.\n<br>You can learn about modulo operation <b> <a href=\"https://codeaccepted.wordpress.com/2014/02/15/output-the-answer-modulo-109-7/\">here</a></b></p>\n\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>d,c</b> \u2264 <b>1000</b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>n1,n2</b> \u2264 <b>20</b></li>\n</ul>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<pre>\n<b>Input:</b>\n1 2 5 1\n<b>Output:</b>\n1\n<br><b>Input:</b>\n3 2 2 1\n<b>Output:</b>\n5\n<br><b>Input:</b>\n3 4 1 1\n<b>Output:</b>\n1\n</pre>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Explanation</h3>\n<p><b>Example case 1.</b> <b>\u201ccdc\u201d<b> is the only awesome arrangement.</p>\n<p><b>Example case 2.</b><b>\u201ccdcdd\u201d</b>, <b>\u201ccddcd\u201d</b>, <b>\u201cddcdc\u201d</b>, <b>\u201cdcddc\u201d</b>, <b>\u201cdcdcd\u201d</b> are the 5 possibilities.</p>\n<p><b>Example case 3.</b> Only 1 arrangement is possible ie <b>\"cdcdcdc\".</b></p>",
